# Taygetan Phoneme Definitions

## Vowel Sounds
- a: /a/ (as in "father")
- e: /e/ (as in "bed") 
- i: /i/ (as in "see")
- o: /o/ (as in "go")
- u: /u/ (as in "moon")
- y: /j/ or /ɪ/ (context dependent glide)

## Consonant Sounds
- n: /n/ (as in "nice")
- t: /t/ (as in "top")
- s: /s/ (as in "sun")
- r: /r/ (lightly rolled 'r')
- l: /l/ (as in "love")
- f: /f/ (as in "flow")
- d: /d/ (as in "dog")
- m: /m/ (as in "mother")
- sh: /ʃ/ (as in "sheep")
- k: /k/ (soft 'k' sound)

## Special Combinations
- ny: /ɲ/ (palatal nasal)
- ky: /c/ + /j/ (palatal stop with glide)
- ty: /t/ + /j/ (alveolar with glide)
- sy: /s/ + /j/ (fricative with glide)
- ly: /ʎ/ + /j/ (lateral with glide)
- my: /m/ + /j/ (nasal with glide)